<p itemprop="description">Data architecture involves designing and managing the structure, policies, and systems that govern how data is collected, stored, integrated, and used across government organizations.</p>

<div class="proficiency-levels">
    <h2>Proficiency Levels</h2>

    <ol class="skill-levels">
        <li>
            <h3>Awareness</h3>
            <p>You can understand the principles of data architecture and recognise the importance of structured data management in government services.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Working</h3>
            <p>You can contribute to data architecture projects, understand data models and schemas, and apply basic data integration principles.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Practitioner</h3>
            <p>You can design comprehensive data architectures, create data models, and establish data integration patterns that support business objectives.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Expert</h3>
            <p>You can lead enterprise data architecture strategy, establish data standards and governance frameworks, and drive digital transformation through data architecture.</p>
        </li>
    </ol>
</div>

